[h1] Tips and Tricks

[h2] Coloured navigation header

[p-]
The coloured link bar at the top of the index page is built from a single
centered paragraph with inline links, each given its own color=.
The separator characters between them are set to the background color
so they vanish - leaving only the coloured labels floating side by side.
[-p]

[code-]
[font id=wide url=podnet://78402/fonts/lilwide.font height=10]

[p- align=center font=wide color=1]
[link- file=1.podweb color=18]HOME[-link] / [link- file=2 color=12]DOCS[-link]
[-p]
[-code]

[p-]
How it works:
color=1 on the paragraph sets the / separators to dark navy, which blends
into the default browser background and makes them invisible. The currently active link (Home in the example above) gets a different color to show the active state.
[-p]

[p-]
If your page has a custom [theme-] background, set the paragraph color=
to match your bg= value so the separators vanish against it too.
[-p]

[p] See [link- file=how-to/colors.podweb]the colors and theming reference[-link] for all available color keys and palette numbers.

